						               													<description>Hell's Corner is an ASL historical study released as an insert in Operations Special Magazine #3. It covers the battles that occured along the Matanikau River on Guadalcanal from August to October 1942.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are five scenarios:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;First Matanikau&amp;quot; is the Marines attempt to secure Matanikau Village shortly after their landing on Guadalcanal.&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Bailey's Demise&amp;quot; recounts the failed attempt by the Marines to dislodge the Japanese from the west bank of the Matanikau.&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Samurai Sunset&amp;quot; features a trapped Japanese Company trying to break out of an encirclement to friendly lines on the west bank of the Matanikau.&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Whaling Good Time&amp;quot; has a group of marines attempting to expand the bridgehead on the Matanikau against a small Japanese rearguard.&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;The Sand Spit&amp;quot; depicts a fresh group of Japanese reinforcements with armored support attempting to break the Marine defenses near Matanikau.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
